<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1229,543,567]" box="[151,1229,543,567]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,291,543,567]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">
<typeStatus box="[151,204,543,567]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1901" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[298,591,543,567]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Akela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladifera">
<emphasis box="[298,455,543,567]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Akela gladifera</emphasis>
Simon, 1901
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[597,614,544,567]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">=</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[620,977,543,567]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladifer">
<emphasis box="[620,822,543,567]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Simonurius gladifer</emphasis>
(Simon, 1901)
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,613,1036]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,368,613,639]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Revised diagnosis.</emphasis>
Among huriines, males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[668,796,614,640]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[668,796,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Simonurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the shortest embolus; in addition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[1237,1365,614,640]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1237,1365,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Simonurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males differ from all other huriines by having a prolateral tegular apophysis (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Galiano, M. E." box="[1020,1178,649,675]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" pagination="285 - 301" refId="ref17400" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1988) Revision de los generos del grupo Hurieae (Araneae, Salticidae). Journal of Arachnology, 15, 285 - 301." type="journal article" year="1988">Galiano 1988</bibRefCitation>
: figs 28, 34). Females differ from those of the remaining huriine genera by having large primary spermathecae, long and thin secondary spermathecae and short copulatory ducts (
<figureCitation box="[622,752,721,748]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–58" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[173,1409,421,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-133@18.[151,1435,417,1845]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 49–58. Simonurius gladifer. Habitus male (MCTP 31078): 49 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 50 ventral view; 51 lateral view; 52 face, frontal view; Habitus female (MCTP 31069): 53 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 54 ventral view; 55 lateral view; 56 face, frontal view, scale bars: 1 mm. Epigyne female (MCTP 31082): 57 ventral view; 58 dorsal view, white arrow: S2* is broken but illustrated and S1 angular axis in anterior region, scale bars: 0.10 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="448">
Figs 57 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[706,720,721,747]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">–</emphasis>
58
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,613,1036]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,757,783]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Note.</emphasis>
In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Galiano, M. E." box="[574,801,757,784]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" pagination="285 - 301" refId="ref17400" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1988) Revision de los generos del grupo Hurieae (Araneae, Salticidae). Journal of Arachnology, 15, 285 - 301." type="journal article" year="1988">Galiano (1988: 296)</bibRefCitation>
compared 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[926,1054,758,784]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[926,1054,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Simonurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Peckham &amp; Peckham, 1896" authorityName="Peckham &amp; Peckham" authorityYear="1896" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Akela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1117,1181,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Akela</emphasis>
Peckham &amp; Peckham, 1896
</taxonomicName>
(Aellurillini: Freyina) and referred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[630,758,794,820]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[630,758,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Simonurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the only genus of huriines with a median apophysis. Since the jumping-spiders of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blackwall" authorityYear="1841" box="[590,700,829,855]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Salticinae">Salticinae</taxonomicName>
do not have true median apophyses (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramirez, M. J." box="[1142,1310,829,855]" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" pagination="1 - 374" refId="ref17756" refString="Ramirez, M. J. (2014) The morphology and phylogeny of dionychan spiders (Araneae: Araneomorphae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 390, 1 - 374. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 821.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Ramírez 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maddison, W. P." pageId="17" pageNumber="448" pagination="231 - 292" refId="ref17522" refString="Maddison, W. P. (2015) A phylogenetic classification of jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae). Journal of Arachnology, 2015, 231 - 292. [http: // www. jstor. org / stable / 24717307]" type="journal article" year="2015">Maddison 2015</bibRefCitation>
), the novel tegular apophysis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[567,695,866,892]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[567,695,866,892]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="448">Simonurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
needs further study in future works, in order to determine its origin and function.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
